description:
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/meshtastic/adapter.c:1578-1621

The switch statement has inconsistent indentation for case blocks:

  switch (packet.kind) {
      case LICHEN_MESHTASTIC_ADAPTER_PACKET_TEXT_MESSAGE_APP:
      adapter->stats.text_packet_count++;        // <-- Not indented under case
      ...
          } else if (info->portnum == MESHTASTIC_PORTNUM_POSITION_APP) {
              if (info->payload == NULL ||        // <-- Extra indentation
                  parse_position_payload(info->payload,
                             info->payload_len,
                             &info->position) < 0) {
                  info->kind =
                      LICHEN_MESHTASTIC_ADAPTER_PACKET_MALFORMED;
              } else {
                  info->kind =
                      LICHEN_MESHTASTIC_ADAPTER_PACKET_POSITION_APP;
              }
          }

This makes the code harder to read and maintain. Some case blocks are indented differently than others.

While not a functional bug, this violates the code style guidelines and should be fixed for consistency.
